article
  mixin labHeader('Foundation 2: Components')
  h3 Duration
  p 20 minutes
  h3 Description
  p Use Foundation to transform the provided HTML to look similar to the following screenshot:
  img(src="assets/raster/foundation-capture-2.png", width="650")
  p The initial links list should be rearranged in a navigation bar. Foundation provides classes for the navigation bar: <b><code>.top-bar</code></b>. The <b><code>.name</code></b> class styles the main link in navigation bar.
  p Several components from Foundation should be used: <b><code>.button</code></b> for buttons, <b><code>.alert</code></b> for alert dialogues and <b><code>.progress</code></b> for progress bars. The rounded border for the text inputs is due to the <b><code>.radius</code></b> or <b><code>.round</code></b> class. The details about these classes could be found at:
  p <a href="http://foundation.zurb.com/docs/">Foundation website</a>